  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">STAR 2: Making the RTI Law work for Inclusive Development</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">. An informed citizenry and media practitioners who are able to engage a responsive government on the RTI Act
2. Increased awareness on the law and how to use it for transparency and accountability
3. Increased information on the importance of the law to our development.
4. A change in the narrative and the perception amongst the populace that the RTI Law is only meant to serve a certain section of our society, the media.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">First, design and develop RTI  information resource centre.
Second, Publish abridged version of the RTI  &amp; simplification and visualisation the RTI Act
Third, Citizens awareness creation
Fourth, media engagements &amp; capacity building for the media and RTI champions</narrative>
  </description>
